  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Czech freelancer visa process takes 3-4 months total from start to arrival. The main steps are: obtain trade license, purchase insurance, gather documents, apply at embassy, wait for processing, then register upon arrival. You MUST apply in person at a Czech embassy.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Obtain Trade License (Živnostenský list)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply at the Czech Trade Licensing Office. You can use a registered agent/representative to do this before you arrive—they provide a Czech address for the application. Cost: ~€30. Processing: 1-5 days. This is required before your visa application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Purchase PVZP or Maxima Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Buy insurance from pvzp.cz or maxi.cz ONLY. You'll receive an insurance certificate to present at your visa appointment. Cost: €500-800/year. Do NOT purchase SafetyWing, Cigna, or other international insurance—they will not be accepted.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather and Verify Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Collect all required documents: criminal record certificate (apostilled), bank statements, passport photos, accommodation proof. Get sworn translations of all non-Czech documents. This can take 2-4 weeks depending on your country's processes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Book Embassy Appointment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Contact the Czech embassy or consulate in your country to schedule an appointment. Wait times vary—some countries have 2-4 week waits. Book early. You MUST apply in person; mail or online applications are not accepted.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Attend Visa Appointment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Bring all original documents plus copies: trade license, PVZP/Maxima insurance certificate, bank statements, criminal record, passport, photos, accommodation proof. Pay the visa fee (~€100). The interview is usually straightforward.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Processing</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Processing takes 60-90 days—one of the longer waits in Europe. The Ministry of Interior reviews your application. They may request additional documents. Your passport stays at the embassy during this time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Collect Visa and Travel</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Pick up your visa at the embassy. The initial long-term visa is typically valid for 1 year. Enter Czech Republic and prepare for the next step.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register with Foreign Police</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 3 WORKING DAYS of arrival, register at the Foreign Police (Cizinecká policie). Bring your passport, visa, and proof of accommodation. If staying in a hotel, they handle this automatically. Private accommodation requires personal registration. Missing this deadline is a violation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Consider using a visa agency:</strong> Many expats use Prague-based visa agencies (€200-500) to handle the trade license application and document preparation. They reduce rejection risk and save significant stress, especially if you don't speak Czech.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

