  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Using SafetyWing, Cigna, or Other International Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-red-700">This is the #1 mistake and most common reason for visa rejection. Czech authorities require insurance from PVZP or Maxima ONLY. SafetyWing, Cigna Global, Allianz Care, BUPA, World Nomads—ALL are rejected. Don't assume your excellent international coverage will be accepted. It won't be.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Missing Foreign Police Registration (3 Working Days)</h3>
        <p class="text-red-700">You MUST register with the Foreign Police (Cizinecká policie) within 3 WORKING days of arrival. Not 3 calendar days—3 working days. If you arrive Friday, Monday/Tuesday/Wednesday are your deadline. Hotels register you automatically. Private accommodation means you must go in person. Miss this and you'll face fines and complications.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Not Starting the Process Early Enough</h3>
        <p class="text-red-700">Processing takes 60-90 days—longer than most European visas. Add time for trade license (1 week), document gathering and apostilles (2-4 weeks), and embassy appointment wait (2-4 weeks). Start 4-5 months before you want to arrive. Don't book flights until you have the visa.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Insufficient Savings in Bank Account</h3>
        <p class="text-red-700">You need approximately €5,000-6,000 visibly in your bank account at time of application. This isn't a fee—you keep it—but it must be clearly visible in your statements. Funds in investment accounts or crypto don't count. Have the cash in a regular bank account for 2-3 months before applying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Skipping Document Apostille/Legalization</h3>
        <p class="text-red-700">Criminal record certificates and other documents often need apostille or superlegalization (depending on your country). Unverified documents will be rejected. Check with the Czech embassy for your country's specific requirements. This process can take 2-4 weeks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

